# The generated client (src/generated) is its own module named `teambattles`, but Kiota wipes that
# dir on every regeneration (`kiota generate --clean-output`). Its go.mod/go.sum are materialized at
# build time by build.sh (`go mod init teambattles`), so they must NOT be committed - committing them
# would leave the working tree dirty after a regen and break the sdk-drift CI job.
src/generated/go.mod
src/generated/go.sum

# go.sum is resolved at build time (`go mod tidy`, network) and not committed; go.work IS committed
# (it is part of the hand-written two-module dev layout that lets `go build ./...` find the local
# generated module).
go.sum
go.work.sum
